To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Maryland Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

FOIA Officer
Office of the Attorney General for Maryland

Dear FOIA Officer,

Pursuant to the Public Information Act, I request access to records sufficient to show the total amount of public funds expended by the Office of the Attorney General in connection with any civil litigation relating to alleged unlawful firearm sales, straw purchasing, or gun trafficking, for the period January 1, 2022 to present.

This request specifically includes records relating to litigation brought by the Maryland & the District of Columbia against Engage Armament LLC, United Gun Shop, and Atlantic Guns.

This request includes, but is not limited to:

Invoices, billing statements, or similar records from any outside counsel retained in connection with such litigation;
Records reflecting payments made to outside counsel, including total amounts paid;
Engagement letters, contracts, or agreements with outside counsel;
Any summaries, spreadsheets, or reports reflecting total litigation costs or expenditures by matter;
Records sufficient to show the total number of hours billed by outside counsel, if maintained;
Records sufficient to show the amount of time expended by in-house personnel (including attorneys, paralegals, or staff), including but not limited to:
a. Timekeeping records, if maintained;
b. Any internal reports or summaries reflecting hours worked on the matter;
c. Any records used to allocate or track staff time to specific cases;
Records sufficient to show the cost or estimated cost of in-house personnel time devoted to such litigation, including any calculations, reports, or methodologies used to determine such costs;
Records reflecting any additional litigation-related expenditures, including but not limited to:
a. Expert witness fees;
b. Consulting services;
c. Investigative services;
d. Travel, lodging, or related expenses;
e. Court costs, filing fees, or transcript costs;
f. Any payments to third-party organizations or contractors providing legal or litigation support services.

If precise cost figures for in-house personnel time are not maintained, I request any records from which such costs could reasonably be estimated, including salary ranges, time allocations, or internal cost accounting methodologies.

If any portion of these records is exempt from disclosure, please provide all reasonably segregable non-exempt portions. If detailed billing narratives or privileged material are exempt, I request that aggregate totals (including hours and amounts) be provided in redacted or summary form.

I request that all responsive records be provided in electronic format where available.

If the cost of processing this request is expected to exceed $50.00, please notify me in advance.

Thank you for your time and consideration.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

James  Manning
